      • getConnections

        Collection<T> getConnections()

      • getActiveConnections

        Collection<T> getActiveConnections()
        Returns all connections bind or not that are currently holding resources on this member. If the connection never successfully finishes with the handshake then it will only be visible through this sub-set.
        Returns:
        Collection of all connections hold on this member

      • registerConnection

        boolean registerConnection(Address address,
                           T connection)
        Registers (ie. stores) the connection for the given remote address. Once this call finishes every subsequent call to getConnection(Address) will return the relevant Connection resource.
        Parameters:
        address - - The remote endpoint to register the connection under
        connection - - The connection to be registered
        Returns:
        True if the call was successful

      • getConnection

        T getConnection(Address address)
        Gets the connection for a given address. If the connection does not exist, it returns null.
        Parameters:
        address - the remote side of the connection
        Returns:
        the found Connection, or none if one doesn't exist

      • getOrConnect

        T getOrConnect(Address address)
        Gets the existing connection for a given address or connects. This call is silent.
        Parameters:
        address - the address to connect to
        Returns:
        the found connection, or null if no connection exists
        See Also:
        getOrConnect(Address, boolean)

      • getOrConnect

        T getOrConnect(Address address,
               boolean silent)
        Gets the existing connection for a given address. If it does not exist, the system will try to connect asynchronously. In this case, it returns null.

        When the connection is established at some point in time, it can be retrieved using the getConnection(Address).

        Parameters:
        address - the address to connect to
        silent - if logging should be done on debug level (silent=true) or on info level (silent=false)
        Returns:
        the existing connection

      • transmit

        boolean transmit(Packet packet,
                 T connection)
        Transmits a packet to a certain connection.

        If this method is called with a null connection, the call returns false.

        Parameters:
        packet - the packet to transmit
        connection - he connection to where the Packet should be transmitted
        Returns:
        true if the transmit was a success, false if a failure (there is no guarantee that the packet is actually going to be received since the packet perhaps is stuck in some buffer; it just means that it's buffered somewhere)
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if the packet is null

      • transmit

        boolean transmit(Packet packet,
                 Address target)
        Transmits a packet to a certain address.

        If the connection to the target doesn't exist yet, the system will try to make the connection. In this case true can be returned, even though the connection eventually can't be established.

        Parameters:
        packet - The Packet to transmit.
        target - The address of the target machine where the Packet should be transmitted.
        Returns:
        true if the transmit was a success, false if a failure.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if packet or target is null.
        See Also:
        transmit(com.hazelcast.nio.Packet, com.hazelcast.nio.Connection)
